The paper deals with the problem of recovering a set of core nodes in a hypergraph, which is a problem in graph theory and network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the practical implementation of the algorithm and its performance on real-world datasets, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses theoretical analysis and machine learning techniques, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CYBER (Cryptography and Security).
